  "text": "Various definitions for haemodynamic response to tracheal intubation have been used in previous studies. The definition previously used by Gan and colleagues, [CITATION_1] with an absolute upper limit of HR instead of a relative increase, better represents the general notion of perioperative tachycardia as risk factor of perioperative cardiac morbidity 20 21 than an absolute or relative HR increase, where the maximal HR after stimulation may still be normal.",
